The paper discusses the potential of quantum finite automata for solving promise problems, which is a topic related to computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also specifically focuses on the use of quantum finite automata with exact acceptance, which falls under the sub-category of quantum computing, cs.QL (Quantum Physics). Additionally, the paper discusses the size of automata, which is related to data structures, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses mathematical proofs and analysis, which is related to logic in computer science, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper discusses the potential of finding more quantum algorithms for other promise problems, which is related to information theory, cs.IT (Information Theory).
